text.section:
A member who is subject to the contributory pension benefit is entitled to the eligibility service to which the member was entitled before the separation from employment if the member:
separated from employment on or before June 30, 1998;
was not entitled to a vested allowance from the Employees' Pension System or the Teachers' Pension System at the time of the separation from employment;
becomes a member who is subject to the contributory pension benefit on or before June 30, 2003;
completes 1 year of employment as a member who is subject to the contributory pension benefit;
did not transfer to the Employees' Pension System or the Teachers' Pension System from the Employees' Retirement System or the Teachers' Retirement System after April 1, 1998; and
applies for the prior eligibility service credit by completing a claim for the service credit and filing it with the Board of Trustees on the form that the Board of Trustees provides.

A member who is subject to the Alternate Contributory Pension Selection is entitled to the eligibility service to which the member was entitled before the separation from employment if the member:
was separated from employment for less than 4 years;
was not entitled to a vested allowance from the Employees' Pension System or the Teachers' Pension System at the time of separation;
becomes a member who is subject to the Alternate Contributory Pension Selection on or before June 30, 2010;
completes 1 year of employment as a member who is subject to the Alternate Contributory Pension Selection;
did not transfer to the Employees' Pension System or the Teachers' Pension System from the Employees' Retirement System or Teachers' Retirement System after April 1, 1998;
applies for the prior eligibility service credit by completing a claim for the service credit and filing it with the Board of Trustees on a form that the Board of Trustees provides; and
deposits into the annuity savings fund the member contributions, if any, that would have been due for the period of service if the member had been subject to the Alternate Contributory Pension Selection, plus regular interest on the contributions.
